race.comment: OUR EXISTENCE (2) is another winning chance for the Durrant yard. Resumed from a 428-day break at Northam and was still short of a run at Belmont following. Will be better for those and has plenty up his sleeve. Maps for the run of the race and the 2kg claim brings him right into it. QUESTIONEVERYTHING (4) is a lightly raced improver from the Wolfe yard. Placed here as favourite on debut and then was backed off the map winning his Maiden easily. Maps for a soft run and Faithfull sticking aboard is a positive. BONNY ROCK (8) was on the speed at Narrogin and demolished the 44 graders by 5.5L. Peaks and will be tough to peg back, holding that form. AMARLIE MISS (7) made plenty of improvement when beaten by a half length at Geraldton. Gets in well with the 3kg claim, and she should be finishing hard.
